Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora at neck join to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Trimmed. Name Andrias. Probably from the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, BIBALEX 0189, which has 'epei' at start, giving one extra letter, suitably filling the space.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1082)
